<HEADLINE> AP Top News at 2 a.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunday, July 2, 2000
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
One Dead After Ohio Terrace Collapses
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   MIDDLE BASS ISLAND, Ohio (AP) -- Two people are dead and dozens injured after
a cement terrace loaded with tourists collapsed at an island winery in Lake Erie
Saturday, authorities said. The collapse left a gaping hole in the floor of the
lakefront terrace at Lonz Winery's century-old main building, a fortresslike
mansion on the National Register of Historic Places. ''The whole deck just
disappeared, it just fell,'' Barbara Kraft, visiting the island from Rochester
Hills, Mich., told WBNS-TV in Columbus. Paramedics estimated 30 people were
critically injured.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
New Government To Be Appointed in Fiji
