   MANZANILLO, Cuba (AP) -- Fidel Castro defiantly warned the next U.S.
president Saturday not to try to defeat his socialist revolution, as the Cuban
government launched a new series of mass demonstrations after Elian Gonzalez's
return. Led by Gen. Raul Castro, head of the Revolutionary Armed Forces and
Fidel Castro's younger brother, a sea of people vigorously waved small red,
white and blue Cuban flags. In rare comments to reporters afterward, Raul Castro
said that media coverage of the battle over Elian had helped Americans better
understand Cuba and its people. Because of that increased understanding, ''the
second chapter will also be a triumph,'' he said.
</P>
