<HEADLINE> Joely Fisher Discusses Celeb Parents  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Joely Fisher says her mother, singer-actress
Connie Stevens, knew how to balance her career and personal life.
Her playboy crooner father, Eddie Fisher, did not.
</P>
<P>
   Fisher, who played the narcissistic Paige on the ABC sitcom
''Ellen,'' said show business and her father, who also was married
to Liz Taylor and Debbie Reynolds, were a toxic mix.
</P>
<P>
   ''It was a very destructive relationship. It's the opposite of
how I was brought up, this feeling that the only way you could
receive love was through being popular,'' said Fisher, 32, in
Sunday's Newsday.
</P>
<P>
   Fisher, who is starring in ''Cabaret'' on Broadway, said she
inherited her wit and her warmth from her mother.
</P>
<P>
   ''My mom's an amazing human being. I was a road baby. I fell
asleep in the bandstand many times over and watched this magical
performer in her beautiful flame dress, making people laugh and
cry,'' she said. ''But she's also the most rounded human being. She
made us know the balance.''
</P>
</TEXT>
