<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newly crowned Miss New York stresses children's health  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WATERTOWN, N.Y. (AP) - Miss New York 2000 is a nursing student
who wants to promote physical fitness, especially among young
people.
</P>
<P>
   Kelly Falgiano, 21, of Amherst was crowned Saturday night. She
said her new title requires working with, and improving, the
community.
</P>
<P>
   ''I plan to get involved in local schools and work with
government officials,'' Falgiano told a press conference on Sunday.
''We need to invest more time in our children's health.''
</P>
<P>
   Falgiano holds an associate degree from Erie Community College
and is working toward a master's degree in nursing.
</P>
<P>
   Over the three-day pageant, 28 young women from around the state
vied for the title, competing in talent, swimsuit, evening wear and
an interview.
</P>
<P>
   ''I dreamed the dream and poured my heart into this,'' Falgiano,
who was last year's first runner-up, said. ''Competing in the Miss
America program is about taking good care of yourself and keeping
up on current events. It's not just standing up on the stage and
being a beautiful woman.''
</P>
<P>
   She will represent the state at the Miss America pageant in
Atlantic City this fall.
</P>
<P>
   Falgiano takes the crown from last year's winner, Brandi
Burkhardt.
</P>
</TEXT>
