<HEADLINE> Third Circuit Court of Appeals judges to hear arguments in Wilmington during convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) - Judges of the 3rd U.S. Circuit Court of
Appeals in Philadelphia will hear oral arguments in Wilmington on
Aug. 1 and 2 during the Republican National Convention.
</P>
<P>
   ''There was concern that if there are demonstrations, the judges
and attorneys might not be able to get through to the courthouse,''
Judge Jane R. Roth said.
</P>
<P>
   The court hears appeals from federal cases in New Jersey,
Pennsylvania and Delaware.
</P>
<P>
   On Aug. 1 and 2, a three-judge panel will hear oral arguments at
the U.S. District Courthouse in Wilmington.
</P>
<P>
   Even if protests don't cause a problem, the 45,000 people
expected in Philadelphia for the convention mean lawyers who
commute to argue cases may not be able to get a hotel, said Jim
Yacucci, appeals court deputy executive.
</P>
</TEXT>
