<HEADLINE> Comets 69, Mercury 58  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON (AP) -- Sheryl Swoopes and Cynthia Cooper each scored 20
points as the three-time defending WNBA champion Houston Comets
beat the Phoenix Mercury 69-58 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Houston has won six straight to improve its league-best record
to 15-2. Tonya Edwards led Phoenix (9-6) with 14 points.
</P>
<P>
   After shooting just 20 percent (6-of-30) from the field in the
first half to fall behind 25-21, the Comets opened the second half
with a 24-2 run. Cooper scored nine points and Tina Thompson had
seven during the spree. Thompson finished with nine points and 11
rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Houston took a 23-point lead, but Phoenix cut it to five with
less than a minute remaining. The Comets sealed the victory with
six consecutive free throws, two by Janeth Arcain and four by
Tiffani Johnson. Johnson finished with 10 points.
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Gillom added 12 points for Phoenix and Lisa Harrison
had 11.
</P>
<P>
   A crowd of 13,865 attended the game at Compaq Center.
</P>
