<HEADLINE> Rangers' Oliver Injures Leg in Home  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Texas Rangers left-hander Darren Oliver
injured his left leg on a nail while moving boxes in his attic
Sunday and went to emergency room, were 12 stitches were needed to
close a cut on his thigh.
</P>
<P>
   Oliver, injured when he lost his balance, is on the Rangers
15-day disabled list and had started throwing off a mound on
Saturday. He was to begin a minor league rehabilitation assignment
later this week.
</P>
<P>
   Texas had hoped Oliver would join the rotation shortly after the
All-Star break. Team physician Dr. John Conway said Oliver's return
might not be affected by Sunday's accident.
</P>
