<HEADLINE> Happyanunoit Wins Beverly Hills  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Even-money favorite Happyanunoit won
the $250,000 Beverly Hills Handicap by three lengths over Sweet
Life on Sunday at Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Happyanunoit, ridden by Brice Blanc, covered 1&AMP;frac14; miles in 1:59
1-5, one-fifth of a second off the stakes record set by Estrapade
in 1986.
</P>
<P>
   The 5-year-old mare carried 121 pounds and paid $4, $3 and
$2.10.
</P>
<P>
   The $150,000 purse pushes the New Zealand-bred Happyanunoit's
career earnings to nearly $1.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   Polaire, ridden by Corey Nakatani, finished third as Astra, the
6-5 second choice who had beaten Happyanunoit in last month's
Gamely Handicap, faded to fourth after setting the early pace.
</P>
<P>
   Sweet Life, ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye and carrying 116
pounds, paid $4.80 and $2.60. Polaire, carrying 116 pounds, paid $3
to show.
</P>
<P>
   The tiring Astra was eventually disqualified and placed last in
the field of five for drifting out and impeding Country Garden in
the stretch.
</P>
</TEXT>
