<HEADLINE> Husband charged in wife's murder; police examine second body  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) - Police have accused a man of killing his
wife and dumping her body in a lake.
</P>
<P>
   Less than an hour later, Ithaca police then found the body of a
man in a gorge. Police said they have no reason to believe the
incidents are related, according to the Ithaca Journal.
</P>
<P>
   Guy Paul Vellake, 35, of Alpine was in Tompkins County Jail
Sunday charged with second-degree murder, Ithaca police said. The
body of his estranged wife, Tammy Vallake, 30, of Moravia was found
in a lake in Stewart Park around 6 a.m. Her car was found nearby.
</P>
<P>
   Her husband was arrested about two hours later.
</P>
<P>
   An autopsy is planned.
</P>
<P>
   The unidentified man's body was found in the Fall Creek gorge,
near where the creek meets the lake in which the woman's body was
found. The cause of death of the man is pending an autopsy.
</P>
<P>
   Fire Department and Ithaca Police said they don't suspect foul
play in his death.
</P>
</TEXT>
