<HEADLINE> Sparks 85, Shock 63  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Mwadi Mabika scored 21 points as the
Los Angeles Sparks extended their franchise-record winning streak
to nine games with an 85-63 victory over Detroit on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Lisa Leslie had 18 points and 12 rebounds for Los Angeles (13-2)
before fouling out with 3:15 to play. DeLisha Milton added 12
points and reserve Allison Feaster had 10.
</P>
<P>
   Wendy Palmer led Detroit (7-8) with 12 points.
</P>
<P>
   Mabika scored 12 points during a 15-2 run that gave the Sparks a
31-14 lead.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks, who are a game behind Houston in the Western
Conference, have won 10 straight at home.
