<HEADLINE> Jersey City father kills two sons, commits suicide  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) - A mother going to pick up her sons from
a visit with their father Sunday discovered that her estranged
husband had killed them and then turned the gun on himself,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Jersey City police confirmed that the father and the boys, ages
5 and 7, died of gunshot wounds to the head. Authorities did not
release a motive or the type of weapon used.
</P>
<P>
   An official reached at the Hudson County Prosecutor's Office
Sunday night would only say the incident is under investigation.
</P>
<P>
   Neighbors said the victims were Oscar Aquieles and his sons,
Oscar, 7, and Brian, 5. A neighbor said the mother, Victoria
Espalliat, forced the door of Aquieles' apartment open after no one
answered.
</P>
<P>
   ''The next thing I heard was all kinds of screaming and
crying,'' neighbor Daisy Pickett told the Star-Ledger of Newark.
''She just kept saying, 'My babies, my babies.'''
</P>
</TEXT>
